\begin_layout Subsection*
6 Costs
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
While the experiment can be conducted as a table-top experiment, many of
 the mirrors need to be specifically designed, as does the mechanical resonator.
 To circumvent these production costs, it is proposed that UWA PhD student
 Haixing Miao and myself conduct the experiment in collaboration with a
 prominent group from the Univeristaire Pierre et Marie Curie, who are one
 of the leaders in parametric cooling.
 Their apparatus and experience will not only cut costs but also give our
 collaboration a strong chance of being the first in the race to the ground
 state.
